This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it focuses on model compression for deep neural networks. It may also belong to computer vision (cs.CV) as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image-related tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. Neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS) are also possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks and pruning techniques.
